headline: Labour Codes trigger showdown, Unions call ‘combative resistance’ on Nov 26
synthesis: This ties into broader market movement and sentiment.

timeline.speaker: chip
timeline.text: "Chip, break down the implications of the unions' combative stance ahead of the showdown on November 26."

timeline.speaker: chip
timeline.text: The upcoming showdown on November 26 highlights the escalating tensions between labor unions and government policies regarding labor codes. As unions prepare for what they describe as "combative resistance," the implications for market stability may be significant. Observers will be keenly watching how this conflict influences worker sentiment and economic conditions.

timeline.text: Turning to another significant development, labour unions have announced a planned response for November 26.
